4.3.1 Spell points
------------------

To _use_ magic, that is, to cast spells and summon spirits, you must
acquire _spell points_. You get spell points in proportion to the
amount of jewels you invest in magical R&D, but _not_ from your money
investment.  Your budget report indicates how many spell points you
will earn from your jewel investment.

   *Please note:* spell points do _not_ accumulate: if you don't use
your spell points, two thirds of them will be lost the next thon. It is
advisable to use all the spell points made in a thon, or to wait and
save up jewels and then invest them all at once.


